Privacy Policy for Invitation Maker App by MK APPS PVT India
Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy outlines how MK APPS PVT ("we", "us", "our" or "Application") collects, uses, maintains, and discloses personal data obtained from users ("User", "you" or "your") of the Invitation Maker mobile application.
Policy Summary
This Application collects various types of Personal Data for specific purposes using the following services:
Advertising
: AdMob collects Tracker, unique device identifiers for advertising (e.g., Google Advertiser ID or IDFA), and Usage Data.
Analytics
: Google Analytics for Firebase gathers Usage Data.
Infrastructure Monitoring
: Crashlytics collects crash data, device information, and Universally unique identifiers (UUID).
Managing Contacts and Sending Messages
: Firebase Cloud Messaging handles various types of Data as specified in its privacy policy.
Platform Services and Hosting
: The Apple App Store and Google Play Store collect Usage Data.
Registration and Authentication
: Firebase Authentication and Sign in with Apple collect email addresses, first names, and last names.
User Database Management
: Data Storage on the owner's server saves designs and resources chosen to be stored in the cloud.
Information on Opting Out of Interest-Based Advertising
Users can opt out of interest-based advertising through settings provided by services like YourOnlineChoices (EU), Network Advertising Initiative (US), Digital Advertising Alliance (US, Canada, Japan), and similar initiatives. The Digital Advertising Alliance offers AppChoices to manage interest-based advertising on mobile apps. Additionally, users can opt out via device settings for mobile phones or general ads settings.
Full Policy
For comprehensive details on each type of Personal Data collected and its usage, refer to specific sections of this privacy policy or explanations provided prior to data collection.
Methods of Data Processing
We employ security measures to prevent unauthorized access, disclosure, modification, or destruction of Personal Data. Processing methods include computer or IT tools, strictly aligned with the specified purposes. Data may be accessible to designated personnel or external parties (e.g., technical service providers, hosting providers) acting as Data Processors, as necessary.
Legal Basis of Processing
Personal Data may be processed based on consent, contractual necessity, legal obligations, vital interests, public task, or legitimate interests pursued by the Owner or third parties.
Place of Data Processing
Data processing occurs at the Owner's operating offices and other locations where parties involved in processing are situated. Transfers of Data to other countries may occur, including to jurisdictions outside your own, subject to applicable laws.
Retention of Personal Data
Personal Data is retained for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected. Further details on specific retention periods may be outlined in applicable sections of this policy.
Information We Collect
Personal Information
We may collect the following personal information when you use our app:
Your name and contact information (such as email address) when you provide it voluntarily.
User-generated content, including logos and designs you create using our app.
Usage and device information, including but not limited to device type, operating system, and app usage patterns.
Non-Personal Information
We may also collect non-personal information, such as anonymized usage statistics and data that does not directly identify you.
How We Use Your Information
We use your personal information for the following purposes:
To provide and improve our logo maker services.
To communicate with you, respond to your inquiries, and provide customer support.
To send you updates, newsletters, and marketing materials (if you have opted in).
To analyze app usage and trends to enhance user experience.
To comply with legal obligations and protect our rights.
Data Deletion
You have the right to request the deletion of your personal information from our systems. To do so, please contact us.
Data Deletion Requests
If you decide to delete your account and associated data, simply navigate to the "Settings" screen within the app and choose the "Delete Account" option. You can also reach out to us directly at
products@mkapps.app
. We'll promptly process your request.
Rights of Users
Users may exercise rights concerning their Personal Data as provided by applicable data protection laws. These rights include access, rectification, erasure, restriction of processing, objection to processing, data portability, and not to be subject to automated decision-making.
California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)
For California residents, specific information about categories of personal information collected, sources, purposes of use, disclosure, sale, opt-out rights, and methods to exercise your rights is detailed in the dedicated CCPA section.
Privacy Rights of Brazilian Users
Brazilian Users have specific privacy rights under Brazilian law, including access to data, correction of inaccurate information, deletion of unnecessary or excessive data, anonymization of data, and data portability.
Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
products@mkapps.app